-----------------
INSTALATION
----------------


Put every archives in ~/pomodoro/ or anywhere you want (but modify the direction in pomodo.py).



-----------------
EXECUTION
----------------
Open a terminal, and then:

$ cd pomodoro
$ python pomodoro.py


You are in the program.
Enter "h" to open the help and know the full-list commands.



You can make a "shortcut" openning a terminal, and writting:

alias pomodoro = "python ~/pomodoro/pomodoro.py"

When you write pomodoro in a terminal, it will execute the program.

Check out that this is temporal, if you want to have it for ever, google it!

